VENDORING PATH (decision recorded per phantasia-dreamerv3/tasks.md task 1.1)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Path (b) was chosen: a SELF-CONTAINED, faithful JAX re-implementation of the
DreamerV3 RSSM world-model core lives in `rssm.py`, DERIVED FROM and ATTRIBUTED
TO danijar/dreamerv3 at the pinned commit above.

Why path (b) and not path (a) (vendoring literal upstream source):

danijar/dreamerv3's RSSM is written against the author's custom research infra
(`ninjax`, `elements`, `embodied`). Those modules are not pip-packaged libraries
and the RSSM source will NOT import standalone without dragging in the entire
training harness (replay buffers, distributed runners, logging side effects,
on-disk checkpointing). Trying to make that research code importable behind a
thin wrapper is a rathole and — critically — several of those code paths write
checkpoints / replay shards to disk, which would violate KAINE's load-bearing
zero-persistence invariant.

`rssm.py` therefore re-implements ONLY the world-model core from the upstream
architecture:
  - encoder MLP  (observation -> embedding)
  - recurrent deterministic state via a GRU cell  (the "h" / deter state)
  - stochastic categorical OR Gaussian latent  (the "z" / stoch state)
  - decoder MLP  (latent -> reconstructed observation)
  - imagination rollout  (prior-only multi-step latent rollout)

It DELIBERATELY EXCLUDES the actor, critic, return head, and reward head.
KAINE's action selection is Nous (pymdp active inference); Phantasia is a pure
world model. There is no reward signal and no policy here by design.

The implementation uses only `jax` + `jax.numpy` (and the stdlib). It does NOT
depend on `einops`, `chex`, `ninjax`, `elements`, or `embodied` at runtime, so
it runs CPU-only under the `[worldmodel]` optional extra. `chex`/`einops` are
declared in that extra for parity with the upstream toolchain and to keep the
door open for future literal-source experiments, but the runnable core here
needs neither.

